{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"## Description\nRe-point the code_health metric specs at the analyzer + snapshot store instead of scanning `src/rebar/**/*.py` and `.github/module-size-limit.txt`, so a non-Python client gets honest Unavailable rather than fabricated zeros. Does NOT touch the CI module-size GATE (separate governance). No LLM/prompt/schema surface is introduced (T8 not-applicable); the only data shapes are the existing `plan_review`-independent metric dicts and the snapshot NDJSON record.\n\n## Mechanism, per metric (G6 — mechanism correctness)\n- `module_size_distribution`, `oversized_module_count`: compute from `AnalyzerResult.loc` + config `size_cap`/`size_near_fraction`. `oversized_module_count` is today a seed stub (`grep -n \"_no_data_yet\" src/rebar/metrics/registry.py` confirms) -> gains a real compute here.\n- `module_size_trend`: reads the TIME SERIES from the existing snapshot store via `rebar.metrics.snapshot.read_snapshots(since, until)`; input = stored records `{ts, record:{max_loc, over_cap_count}}`; output = ordered `[{ts, value}]`; `Unavailable` when zero snapshots in range. Rationale: trend REQUIRES history, and the NDJSON snapshot store is the only historical source already present (`test -f src/rebar/metrics/snapshot.py`), so no new persistence is invented.\n- `cap_change_events`: tracks edits to `.github/module-size-limit.txt`, a rebar-governance artifact with NO client analogue. DECISION: DEREGISTER the spec from the portable registry (remove from `register()`), documented in the ticket-close note. Rationale: keeping a rebar-path-specific metric contradicts the epics portability goal; it can live as a rebar-only opt-in later. Deregistration is the minimal correct mechanism (vs. leaving a metric that fabricates/raises on clients).\n\n## Grounding (E4/G1G2 — verified)\n- CONFIRMED `grep -n \"module-size-limit\\\\|src.*rebar.*rglob\\\\|_read_cap\" src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py`: the hardcodes live at :35 (`_LIMIT_FILE`), `_read_cap` :75, scan root `src/rebar` :93, and `cap_change_events` :167 registered ~:272.\n- Existing tests pin the OLD behavior and MUST be updated: `tests/unit/test_git_metrics.py`, `tests/unit/test_git_metrics_heldout.py`, `tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py`. `analyzer.py` is from 3b30 (depends_on) — consumed, not created.\n\n## Acceptance criteria (observable + proving command)\n- [ ] No metric reader references the old hardcodes. PROVE: `! grep -Eq \"src/rebar|module-size-limit.txt\" src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py src/rebar/metrics/registry.py`.\n- [ ] `cap_change_events` no longer registered. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py::test_cap_change_events_deregistered` (asserts the id absent from the rendered registry).\n- [ ] Unconfigured analyzer -> Unavailable, NOT `{count:0,max_loc:0}` at confidence=high, NO leaked errno. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py::test_foreign_repo_honest_unavailable`.\n- [ ] `module_size_trend` returns an ordered series from snapshots (Unavailable when none). PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/metrics/test_module_size_trend.py`.\n- [ ] git-delta + agent_process metrics unchanged; updated git_metrics tests green. PROVE: `pytest -q tests/unit/test_git_metrics.py tests/unit/test_git_metrics_heldout.py`.\n\n## Dependencies: 3b30, 18f9, 21fb, 3ba0 (recorded depends_on edges).\n## Files: src/rebar/metrics/git_metrics.py, src/rebar/metrics/registry.py, tests/unit/test_git_metrics.py, tests/unit/test_git_metrics_heldout.py, tests/interfaces/test_metrics_cli.py, tests/unit/metrics/test_module_size_trend.py (new)\n## Scope: M-L"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784533544933999001,"uuid":"e165a37c-57e5-4795-b766-b31a84a57219"}